# ============================================================================
# apps/web/.env.example
#
# Copy to `apps/web/.env` (which is gitignored) and adjust values:
#     cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env
#
# TanStack Start / Vite environment variables.
#
# Namespace convention (enforced by Vite + Nitro):
#   VITE_PUBLIC_<NAME>  -> exposed to the browser bundle via
#                          `import.meta.env.VITE_PUBLIC_*`. Never put secrets
#                          here: anything VITE_PUBLIC_* ends up in client JS.
#   <NAME>              -> server-only (Nitro/SSR runtime). Safe for tokens,
#                          private API keys, internal URLs.
#
# No web env variables are required at this step (017). Add real keys when
# the public site starts calling the API in Track 4 (e.g. VITE_PUBLIC_API_URL).
# ============================================================================
